events.name: Golden State Warriors at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner made three free throws with 12.2 seconds left and dunked on an inbounds play for the final points, leading the Orlando Magic to a 94-90 win over the Golden State Warriors on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors fall to Magic 94-90; Suns clinch 1st in Pacific

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Trae Young got a pregame hug from Spike Lee, so there was at least a little love for him inside Madison Square Garden.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 45 in return to MSG, Hawks beat Knicks 117-111

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 25 points and 17 rebounds in his return to action and the Milwaukee Bucks extended their recent mastery of the Chicago Bulls with a 126-98 blowout on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo returns, Bucks roll to 126-98 win over Bulls

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic bounced back from a rare poor shooting performance, scoring 30 points to lead the Denver Nuggets to a 127-115 win over the Los Angeles Clippers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Nuggets bounce back with 127-115 win over LA Clippers
